UBC iGEM 2022 - Differential Expression Analysis

Differential Expression Workflow:

  1. Read in the Data
  2. Create a DGEList Object
  3. Filter
  4. Normalize
  5. Estimate Dispersions
  6. Differential Expression

As there are only a few samples, it’s difficult to estimate the dispersion accurately for each gene, so we need a way of “sharing” information between genes. Possible solutions include:

  • Using a common estimate across all genes (common dispersion).

  • Fitting an estimate based on the mean-variance trend across the dataset, such that genes w/ similar abundances have similar variance estimates (trended dispersion).

  • Computing a genewise dispersion (tagwise dispersion)

plotBCV(d)

et <- exactTest(d, pair=c("HD_6h","ctrl"))
# just looking at the top 100 hits for now
HD6h_vs_ctrl <- topTags(et, n=1000)
de <- decideTestsDGE(et, adjust.method="BH", p.value=0.001)
summary(de)
##        ctrl-HD_6h
## Down         2711
## NotSig      14660
## Up           2348
detags <- rownames(d)[as.logical(de)] 
plotSmear(et, de.tags=detags)
abline(h = c(-2, 2), col = "blue")

hist(et$table[,"PValue"], breaks=50, xlab="P-value", main="P-value Distribution")

sigResults <- et$table[et$table$PValue<0.001,]
dim(sigResults)
## [1] 5863    3
# up-regulated and down-regulated gene expression in HD_6h group compared to ctrl
sigReg <- HD6h_vs_ctrl$table[HD6h_vs_ctrl$table$FDR<0.01,]
sigUpReg <- filter(sigReg, logFC < -1)
sigDownReg <- filter(sigReg, logFC > 1)
sigUpReg <- sigUpReg[order(sigUpReg$logFC),]
sigDownReg <- sigDownReg[order(sigDownReg$logFC, decreasing=TRUE), ]
print(sigUpReg)

upRegGenes <- rownames(sigUpReg)
downRegGenes <- rownames(sigDownReg)
plantsDatabase <- useMart(biomart = 'plants_mart', dataset="taestivum_eg_gene", host = 'https://plants.ensembl.org')
filters <- listFilters(plantsDatabase)
filters
attributes <- listAttributes(plantsDatabase)
attributes
# after filtering, LC (low confidence) genes are removed as they aren't present in the reference dataset
go_terms_upreg <- getBM(attributes = c("ensembl_gene_id", "description", "go_id", "name_1006", "definition_1006", "namespace_1003", "plant_reactome_pathway", "plant_reactome_reaction", "gene_biotype", "uniprotsptrembl"), filter = "ensembl_gene_id", values=upRegGenes, mart=plantsDatabase)

go_terms_upreg
upregMolFunc <- go_terms_upreg %>% filter(namespace_1003 == "molecular_function")
upRegMolFuncCounts <- upregMolFunc %>%
  group_by(name_1006) %>%
  summarise(n = n()) %>%
  mutate(frequency = n/sum(n) * 100)

upRegMolFuncCounts <- slice_head(arrange(upRegMolFuncCounts, desc(frequency)), n=10)
upRegMolFuncCounts
upRegMolFuncCounts$name_1006 = with(upRegMolFuncCounts, reorder(name_1006, frequency))

top10upRegMolFunc <- upRegMolFuncCounts %>%
ggplot(aes(x=name_1006, y=frequency, fill=name_1006, alpha=0.5)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", width=0.4) + coord_flip() +  labs(title = "Top 10 Terms", y = "Percentage of Upregulated Genes in HD6h Wheat", x = "Molecular Function") + theme(legend.position="none")
